        <num>CC 3481</num>
        <heading>3481.  Presumption of good faith</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3481.  Presumption of good faith
Good faith is presumed.  Neither error of fact nor error of law defeats this presumption.  This presumption is rebutted on proof that the possessor knows, or should know, that he is not owner of the thing he possesses.</p>
        </content>
